article.description: Chris Knight tallied 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead Dartmouth to a 75-53 win over Cornell on Saturday night.
article.headline: Knight leads Dartmouth over Cornell 75-53
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Chris Knight tallied 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead Dartmouth to a 75-53 win over Cornell on Saturday night. Knight made 8 of 10 shots. James Foye had 17 points for Dartmouth (9-14, 2-6 Ivy League). Aaryn Rai added 13 points. Terrance McBride had 17 points for the Big Red (5-16, 2-6). Bryan Knapp added 10 points. Kobe Dickson had three blocks. Dartmouth faces Penn at home on Friday. Cornell plays Yale at home on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
